Computational Objects have ...
* a name
* a value
* a location
* other properties

Files are computational objects
* name e.g. my_program.c
* value = contents of file
* location = directory containing file
* other properties
  - access rights, owner, size, update time, ...

Variables are simple computational objects
* name e.g. total
* value ... whatever was last assigned
* location = address in memory (more later)
* other properties
  - type ... tells how to interpret value







C program ...
* set of functions
* possibly in multiple *.c files
* #include'ing various "libraries"
* one file must contain main()








Typical program structure ...
* get input values
* process inputs to compute result
* display result






